C# - Programming

Type Casting:

When you assign the value of one data type to another data type.

In C#: 

1. Implicit Casting: automatically--> convert small type to large type size

	char --> int
	int-->long
	float-->double

2. Explicit Casting: convert large type to small type size

	double-->float
	long-->int
	int-->char
	
Type Conversion Predefined Methods:

Convert.ToInt32(int): int : 4bytes
Convert.ToString
Convert.ToInt64(long): long : 8bytes
Convert.ToDouble
Convert.ToBoolean